                    "company": "ASML",
                    "description": "From October 1st 2007 until June 2013 I was assigned as an equipment engineer computer systems and software to these internal projects at ASML:\n\nHolistic lithography project.\nI gave support to the local field engineers when there were any software issues at the off tool application servers and based on my experience solving these issues I defined the software service requirements for a new X86/VMware/Linux platform for a new generation off tool application servers. A first pilot system of this high available and scalable computer platform has been introduced in the field at the end of 2011. The roll-out of this platform to all customers continues in 2012 and beyond.\n\nTwinscan project:\nI was working at the data handling host and Voyager project. With these projects ASML moved from SUN/Solaris to X86/Linux computing platforms for all scanners.\n\n450 mm project:\nAs an equipment engineer software I defined the reliability, availability, manufacturability and serviceabilty requirements for the development  of a new scanner platform for the production of 450 mm wafers. I made some design proposals for software and computer systems to get a higher availability and serviceabilty of this new scanner platform.",
                    "title": "Equipment engineer computer systems and software",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
